description:
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span&gt;Consultant Psychologist (Cancer &amp; Palliative Care &amp; Clinical Manager for Health Psychology&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A rare and exciting opportunity to lead psychological aspects of cancer and palliative care provision alongside acting as Trust Lead for Health Psychology and clinical manager for a small Health Psychology department.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The clinical component (approx. 0.6 wte) involves delivering NICE Level 4 psychological interventions, supervision and consultations with colleagues of many professions and a range of teaching opportunities. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post is long-established, well integrated with local cancer and palliative care services, and is well respected within the organisation and by other providers (e.g. local hospice).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You’ll also lead a small Health Psychology service, and be the Trust’s Lead for Health Psychology – advising the organisation at a senior level on provision of psychologically appropriate care &amp; development of staff wellbeing initiatives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a great chance for an experienced Cancer &amp; Palliative Care specialist to use the highest level of clinical, leadership and service management skills to make a genuine difference to the experience of people with cancer and other serious illnesses, and to the staff who support them. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This all takes place in a working environment that is small enough to be flexible, and where individuals can have a great impact. Herefordshire itself offers the many benefits of a semi-rural setting ( eg quality of life and relative affordability of housing), and also the related service challenges of geographical access, deprivation and diversity issues which may be different to urban settings, but are just as important in service provision.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If this feels like potentially the right move for you, please do get in touch to discuss further.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Contact: Dr Ray Owen, Consultant Clinical Psychologist &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;ray.owen@wvt.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;, 01432 347697&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;8b&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We’re looking for a Clincal Psychologist /Neuropsychologist to provide expert input to Wye Valley Trust’s community focussed Brain Injury and Stroke Rehab services. The post needs someone who can bring strong neuropsychology skills and experience, and who enjoys close, flexible multiprofessioanl working and lots of direct patient contact, both individually and in groups Formal neuropsychological assessment skills are essential, though delivery of the service is also supported by an Assistant Psychologist working under the post-holder’s supervision.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
